          "body": "The psalm names the ideological engine of the oppression in 94:7: *They have said, 'The Lord does not see, nor does the God of Jacob pay heed.'* This is not atheism — the wicked know God's name and Israel's covenant title ('God of Jacob'). It is **practical deism**: God exists but is inattentive, absent, or indifferent to historical events. The oppressors have constructed a theology that licenses their behavior. The psalmist's rebuttal in 94:8-11 is not an emotional appeal but a logical argument from creation. The rhetorical questions of 94:9 are devastating: *He who planted the ear, does He not hear? He who formed the eye, does He not see?* The argument is a fortiori — from the greater to the lesser. If God is the Creator of the very faculties of perception, it is absurd to imagine that He lacks those faculties Himself. A sculptor is not blind to the statue he carved. The Creator of hearing hears. The Creator of sight sees. The oppressors' theology collapses under the weight of their own creaturely existence."
